    <div id="artwork-details">
    <div id="tombstone">

    <p>    Veniamin Markovich Briskin<br />
(born Romny, 1906; died Moscow, 1982)<br />
    </p>
    <h3><em>How Vasia Terkin "Disguised" Himself from the Fascists</em>, 1941</h3>

    <p>
    Offset lithograph<br />    307 x 884 mm<br />    Text under the helmet hanging on the wall:<br />
The remains of Mannerheim.<br />
<br />
Text under the figure at center reads: <br />
Vasia Terkin<br />
<br />
The poem:<br />
1. Who is this in an army helmet,<br />
in full battle dress?<br />
It is everyone’s favorite,<br />
Vasia Terkin, our hero.<br />
<br />
Around him are fragments of a bunker,<br />
A heap of Finnish epaulettes<br />
That is Vasia’s work.<br />
The remnants of his triumphs.<br />
2. As soon as the golden sun<br />
Rose over the horizon<br />
The front lines saw<br />
The hero Vaasia Terkin.<br />
<br />
He smiled to his friends,<br />
Brave frontline soldiers all.<br />
“Hello Vasia” roared the regiments<br />
In a loud peal of thunder.<br />
3. The same day Vasia Terkin<br />
Proved himself during reconnaissance:<br />
He cut branches off a willow<br />
And stuffed them under his straps.<br />
4. He lies watching vigilantly<br />
Ready to meet the enemy.<br />
Five soldiers hidden behind a hillock<br />
Wait with Vasia for the enemy.<br />
5. The Fascists advance.<br />
They are tired after the long road. <br />
They see the shade of the bush <br />
And decide to take a rest.<br />
<br />
They sit down and take out a bag<br />
Rings, brooches and watches,<br />
Two silver tumblers<br />
And the remains of a sausage.<br />
6. Six of them sit and<br />
Eat on the hillock.<br />
Suddenly Vasia stands up<br />
Along with the willow bush.<br />
<br />
Five Facists are killed<br />
and the last surrenders.<br />
And the bandit is delivered to<br />
The nearest headquarters in village N.<br />
<br />
 Center, below captions: <br />
Drawing by V. Briskin.  Verses by S. Marshak.<br />
State Publishing House Iskusstvo<br />
Moscow 1941 Leningrad<br />
<br />
Right, below captions:<br />
Issue 1. Printshop Krasnyi pechatnik Moscow, 25th of October Street 5. Order 972. Circulation 50,000.<br />    Ne boltai! Collection, Obj: 203889</p>
        
        <!--<p id="dept-gallery">--><!--<br />-->
         <!--</p>-->
    </p>
    </div><!--/tombstone-->

